    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1953-04-02T21:10:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1953-04-02T21:10:00-05:00" n="214"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d214">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">320/4–253: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The United States Representative at the United Nations</hi>
                        (<persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1" type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Lodge</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Department of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#left">
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">confidential</hi>
                        <lb/>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">priority</hi>
                    </seg>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">New York</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1953-04-02T21:10:00-05:00"
                            >April 2, 1953—9:10 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <gloss target="#t_Delga1">Delga</gloss> 527. Re mechanics <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                        >GA</gloss> action appointing new <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss>–<gloss
                        target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss>.</p>
                <p>In meeting of <persName corresp="#p_CORDIERAW1">Cordier</persName>, <persName
                        corresp="#p_STAVROPOULOSCA1">Stavropoulos</persName> (<gloss target="#t_UN1"
                        >UN</gloss>), <persName>Vallat</persName> (<gloss target="#t_UK1"
                    >UK</gloss>) and <persName corresp="#p_HYDEJN1">Hyde</persName>, mechanics of
                        <gloss target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> action appointing new <gloss
                        target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss>–<gloss target="#t_UN1">UN</gloss> was
                    discussed. General procedure is to be simple, have opportunity for <persName
                        corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName> to present valedictory and offer new
                        <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> same terms of appointment as <persName
                        corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName>. This would include five-year
                    appointment, the appointment being open at the end of that period for a further
                    five-year term.</p>
                <pb facs="0478" n="450" xml:id="pg_450"/>
                <list>
                    <label>1.</label>
                    <item>First item of plenary afternoon of 7 April will be <gloss target="#t_SYG1"
                            >SYG</gloss> item. President will read letter of resignation of
                            <persName corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName>, dated November 10, 1952,
                        and <gloss target="#t_SC1">SC</gloss> recommendation of <persName
                            corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1">Hammarskjold</persName>.</item>
                    <label>2.</label>
                    <item>In open meeting President will put to vote <persName
                            corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1">Hammarskjold</persName>’s name with secret
                        ballot—waiving closed meeting provision of rule 140.</item>
                    <label>3.</label>
                    <item>Plan is to circulate as Canadian draft resolution following text, probably
                        3 April but not later than 6 April. This is simplest way of providing for
                        new term of office, retirement rights and any other benefits <persName
                            corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName> now enjoys.
                            <persName>Vallat</persName> will tomorrow clear this with French and ask
                        them to clear with Soviet delegation, assuming Canada approves this draft:
                            <quote rend="blockquote">
                            <p>
                                <hi rend="italic">Begin verbatim text.</hi> “Recalling resolution 11
                                (I) of 24 January 1946 and paragraph 32 of <gloss target="#t_GA1"
                                    >GA</gloss> resolution 13 (I) of 13 February 1946,</p>
                            <p>“Decides that the terms of appointment of the second <gloss
                                    target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss> shall be the same as those of the
                                first <gloss target="#t_SYG1">SYG</gloss>.” <hi rend="italic">End
                                    verbatim text.</hi>
                            </p>
                        </quote>
                    </item>
                    <label>4.</label>
                    <item>Canadian draft will be put to vote.</item>
                    <label>5.</label>
                    <item>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName> will make valedictory though
                        technically he continues in office until <persName
                            corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1">Hammarskjold</persName> takes oath. US and
                        others will have opportunity to express appreciation of <persName
                            corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName>’s efforts.</item>
                    <label>6.</label>
                    <item>President will indicate <persName corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1"
                            >Hammarskjold</persName> arrives New York 9 April and will take oath on
                        10 April in plenary.</item>
                    <label>7.</label>
                    <item>On 10 April in presence of Council Presidents, Vice Presidents and
                            <persName corresp="#p_LIETH1">Lie</persName>, President of <gloss
                            target="#t_GA1">GA</gloss> will administer oath to <persName
                            corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1">Hammarskjold</persName>, whose term at that
                        point legally begins. <persName corresp="#p_HAMMARSKJOLDD1"
                            >Hammarskjold</persName> today telegraphed <persName corresp="#p_LIETH1"
                            >Lie</persName> he would remain at headquarters some weeks before
                        winding up his affairs in Sweden.</item>
                </list>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <persName corresp="#p_LODGEHCJ1">
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Lodge</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
